<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2003-07-19</DATELINE><TITLE>WHO Framework Convention on Tobacco Control: development of an evidence based global public health treaty</TITLE><BODY>Many health problems require international action, but getting governments to agree on strategies for prevention or treatment is difficult. By making use of scientific evidence on the effects of tobacco, the member states of WHO have negotiated their first global health treaty. If the treaty can be implemented effectively, it could act as a possible model for tackling other health issues&#3;</BODY></TEXT>